Seeing as the main topic here seems to be about City I have mixed emotions, my first reaction was to be glad about their ban because I’d read too many bitchy comments from City fans in recent years who conveniently forget they’d be nowhere without the huge financial backers who enabled them to acquire a top coach and players . Then I remembered that this ban will most likely benefit Spurs as I’m guessing now 5th place will bring Champions League football (assuming City finish top 4)
For this reason, the ban isn’t such a great thing for us non City fans 😂

snippet.textDisplay:
Let's not be too hasty in our judgements here. I know what our reactions would have been if the results were the other way around.

As much as we should encourage and applaud the "underdog coach" for his zeal, focus, innovativeness, communication and yes.... English (Lol, I had to say it), I still feel we need to be careful in assuming too much in what he can deliver. It's too early for him to be fully assessed after just a few games (win, draw or lose).

We shouldn't raise our expectations too high. It is his first season. He would need lots time as a lot of things are currently working against him: (lack of funds, crop of players and his inexperience as a top coach)

Still, I give him THUMBS UP 👍🏾 for his efforts so far. We would stand behind him through thick and thin and HOPE he drives the club to the glory it once was 🤞🏾,

Enough said: WELL DONE ARTETA! WELL DONE ARSENAL! 👍🏾
